th America. This is the first overview of a history that began during the French Regime and continued, through many twists and turns, up to the turn of the twenty-first century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aJewszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 0aJewszQuébec (Province)xHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aJewish Culture.  aJewish History.  aMontreal.  aQuébec Province.  aRelations with French Canada.1 aAnctil, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWoodsworth, Judith Weisz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311127221408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021z978311127464540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780776629490?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780776629490423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780776629490/original  a978-3-11-127221-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-127464-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2021b2021  aGBV-deGruyter-alles